2. CREATIVE CONTENT & INTELLECTUAL PROPERTY
───────────────────────────────────────────

The following are considered "Creative Content":

* Characters
* Story, lore, and worldbuilding
* Names, concepts, and settings
* Music, melodies, and themes (unless otherwise stated)
* Visual designs and ideas

Permission is GRANTED to create non-commercial fan works, including but
not limited to:

* fangames
* fan animations and videos
* fan art
* narrative or transformative projects
* mod, steam workshop content or similar free addons

Provided that:

* Proper credit to "TrafkHop Entertainment™" is given
* The work is clearly marked as unofficial / fan-made
* No claim of ownership over the original IP is made
* The content is not used for hateful, harassing, or illegal purposes
* The fan work constitutes a genuinely original creative work — it must
  not replicate, closely imitate, or substantially reproduce the structure,
  gameplay systems, level design, art style, or overall presentation of
  any TrafkHop Entertainment™ project to such a degree that it could
  reasonably be mistaken for, or serves as a direct substitute for, an
  official release. Fan works that are functionally equivalent to, or
  merely cosmetically altered versions of, an original TrafkHop
  Entertainment™ project are NOT permitted under this section and are
  considered infringing copies, not fan works.

Where a TrafkHop Entertainment™ project incorporates third-party
creative material subject to its own license (e.g., SCP Foundation
content under CC BY-SA 3.0), any fan works based on or derived from
that specific project may additionally be subject to the terms of
that third-party license. TrafkHop Entertainment™ will indicate
clearly on a per-project basis when such third-party material is
present and which license applies to it.

It is the responsibility of fan creators to review and comply with
all applicable third-party licenses for the specific project they
are basing their work on.

